Q 34. Find First and Last Position of Element in Sorted Array ?
Medium
Topics
premium lock icon
Companies
Given an array of integers nums sorted in non-decreasing order, find the starting and ending position of a given target value.

If target is not found in the array, return [-1, -1].

You must write an algorithm with O(log n) runtime complexity.

 

Example 1:

Input: nums = [5,7,7,8,8,10], target = 8
Output: [3,4]
Example 2:

Input: nums = [5,7,7,8,8,10], target = 6
Output: [-1,-1]
Example 3:

Input: nums = [], target = 0
Output: [-1,-1]
 

Constraints:

0 <= nums.length <= 105
-109 <= nums[i] <= 109
nums is a non-decreasing array.
-109 <= target <= 109
///////////////////////////////////// Kotlin solve ////////////////

class Solution {
    fun searchRange(nums: IntArray, target: Int): IntArray {
        // Step 1: Pehli position dhoondo
        val first = findBound(nums, target, isFirst = true)
        
        // Agar pehla hi nahi mila, toh matlab number exist hi nahi karta
        if (first == -1) {
            return intArrayOf(-1, -1)
        }
        
        // Step 2: Aakhri position dhoondo
        val last = findBound(nums, target, isFirst = false)
        
        return intArrayOf(first, last)
    }

    // Helper Function: Binary Search Logic
    // isFirst = true matlab hum Left side check karenge (Start dhoondne ke liye)
    // isFirst = false matlab hum Right side check karenge (End dhoondne ke liye)
    private fun findBound(nums: IntArray, target: Int, isFirst: Boolean): Int {
        var start = 0
        var end = nums.size - 1
        var result = -1

        while (start <= end) {
            val mid = start + (end - start) / 2

            if (nums[mid] == target) {
                result = mid // Position mil gayi, store kar lo
                
                if (isFirst) {
                    end = mid - 1 // Aur Left mein dhoondo
                } else {
                    start = mid + 1 // Aur Right mein dhoondo
                }
            } else if (nums[mid] < target) {
                start = mid + 1 // Target right mein hai
            } else {
                end = mid - 1 // Target left mein hai
            }
        }
        return result
    }
}
